From: Vincent Fortier <th0ma7@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 01 Jun 2026
Subject: [PATCH] transcoding/qsv: always pin B-frame count (disable aggressive default)

setup_baseline_opts() only set "bf" when (low_power == 0 && desired_b_depth), so
with the default (0) the qsv encoder used its own default. For hevc_qsv that is
aggressive pyramid B-frames (GopRefDist=5, BRefType=pyramid, confirmed via ffmpeg
verbose), whose reorder delay makes decoded frames arrive late -- VLC logs
"picture is too late to be displayed (missing 20-38 ms)" -- and produces visible
pixellation on live content. h264_qsv and the VAAPI encoders (which set bf=0
explicitly) were unaffected.

Pin the B-frame count unconditionally so the encoder never falls back to its
aggressive default:
 - low-power (VDEnc) path: force bf=0 (B-frames are frequently unsupported there),
   regardless of desired_b_depth;
 - normal path: use desired_b_depth (default 0 -> no B-frames, matching VAAPI;
   set it >0 in the profile to re-enable B-frames).

ffmpeg check (Apollo Lake, iHD): default -> GopRefDist=5/pyramid; -bf 0 ->
GopRefDist=1/off, same ~1.7x encode speed.

Suggested-by: Claude Opus 4.8 (Anthropic AI <https://anthropic.com>)
Signed-off-by: Vincent Fortier <th0ma7@gmail.com>

--- src/transcoding/codec/codecs/libs/qsv.c.orig	2026-05-19 20:37:17.000000000 +0000
+++ src/transcoding/codec/codecs/libs/qsv.c	2026-06-01 13:15:00.000000000 +0000
@@ -259,10 +259,17 @@
  */
 static int
 setup_baseline_opts(const tvh_codec_profile_qsv_t *self, AVDictionary **opts, enum CODEC codec){
-    if ((self->low_power == 0) && (self->desired_b_depth)) {
-        // max_b_frames
-        AV_DICT_SET_INT(LST_QSV, opts, "bf", self->desired_b_depth, AV_DICT_DONT_OVERWRITE);
-    }
+    // Always pin the max B-frame count for QSV so the encoder never falls back to
+    // its aggressive default (hevc_qsv: GopRefDist=5, BRefType=pyramid), whose
+    // reorder delay makes frames arrive late ("picture is too late to be displayed")
+    // and degrades live quality (pixellation).
+    //  - low-power (VDEnc): B-frames are frequently unsupported, so force bf=0
+    //    regardless of desired_b_depth.
+    //  - normal path: use desired_b_depth (default 0 -> no B-frames, matching the
+    //    VAAPI encoders; set it >0 in the profile to re-enable B-frames).
+    AV_DICT_SET_INT(LST_QSV, opts, "bf",
+                    self->low_power ? 0 : self->desired_b_depth,
+                    AV_DICT_DONT_OVERWRITE);
     if (self->b_strategy) {
         AV_DICT_SET_INT(LST_QSV, opts, "b_strategy", self->b_strategy, AV_DICT_DONT_OVERWRITE);
     }
